    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI'm reporting this super early because the change isn't even on nightly, I just found it when working on #24890.\r\n\r\nUsing the tippy-top of `master`, opening the tree inspector causes the error below and the first line in the buffer is removed.\r\n\r\n```\r\nError detected while processing CursorMoved Autocommands for \"<buffer=53>\":\r\nError executing lua callback: runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/dev.lua:372: Invalid 'end_col': out of range\r\nstack traceback:\r\n\t[C]: in function 'nvim_buf_set_extmark'\r\n\truntime/lua/vim/treesitter/dev.lua:372: in function <runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/dev.lua:368>\r\n```\r\n\r\nUndoing #24824 (cc @bfredl) makes the error go away and the inspector to behave as expected.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Build the `master` branch of this repo.\r\n2. Open any file.\r\n3. Run `:InspectTree`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nFor no errors to occur and for the tree inspector to not modify the inspected buffer.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nN/A\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nMac Ventura 13.5\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.28.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
